snippet.textDisplay: I get that Chris had friends and family and coworkers traumatized. But since 2007 going on 13 years the internet wrestling fans have been obsessed with glorifying him and insisting he go in the Hall of Fame. I watched him in WCW and WWF.  He was ok. Not my personal favorite considering I was more amused with some of the comical villains and personalities than straight scientific wrestling. He was talented. I watched him on tv.  But then the tragedy happened. And the WWE rightly moved on as did I . But with the exception of friends, family and close coworkers yes absolutely this  Benoit obsession praises and glorifies murder . Or at the very least makes 15 year old wrestling matches more important than a real life homicide of a wife and child.

snippet.textDisplay: Chris Benoit inspired Jericho.. Jericho, like him or not, is probably in the top 5 greatest wrestlers of all time. No one is better on the mic (you could argue that maybe the rock was, but that's the only one that could be), his in ring ability is fucking fantastic, hes got all the major accolades and accomplishments and achievements one could hope to obtain in professional wrestling, etc. Everyone knows who Chris Jericho was. I remember he was a heal in wcw and I was a kid when they were going strong, but I always thought he was underrated and should have been in the spotlight. Especially during his wcw television title run. Then when he came to the WWF, he went into the stratosphere. Amazing talent, and that shows you how important Benoit was if he inspired people like Jericho. I hate that he did what he did, but he was great at what he did. He should never be honored with a hall of fame induction, though. Ever.

snippet.textDisplay: Gasping is an indication that the brain is still alive and it tells you that if you start and continue uninterrupted chest compressions, the person has a high chance of surviving. The challenge is to educate bystanders that if they are helping someone in cardiac arrest, not to mistake gasping for breathing. Contrary as it may seem, a person who is gasping is not OK – they need chest compressions. Bystanderinitiated CPR has been shown to be a cardiac arrest victim’s only chance of survival until an automated external defibrillator (AED) or the paramedics get to the scene.
